===Bradley (2007), He (1983)===
The ''Encyclopedia of the World's Endangered Languages'' groups Gelao into five subdivisions.<ref name="Moseley">Bradley, David. 2007. "East and Southeast Asia." In Moseley, Christopher (ed). ''Encyclopedia of the World's Endangered Languages''. New York: Routledge.</ref>

*'''Hakhi (<U+54C8><U+7ED9> Hagei, ''{{IPA|ha<U+02E5><U+02E7>kei<U+02E7>}}'', Green Gelao)''': west-central [[Guizhou]], western [[Guangxi]], southeastern [[Yunnan]], northern [[Vietnam]] - including Yangliu (<U+6768><U+67F3>) variety in [[Renhuai County]]; '''southwestern''' Gelao of Sanchong (<U+4E09><U+51B2>) and Qinglong (<U+9752><U+9F99>). Hagei varieties are also spoken in Ma'ao (<U+9EBB><U+51F9><U+6751>), Guanling County (<U+5173><U+5CAD><U+53BF>), Pomao (<U+5761><U+5E3D>) in Zhenfeng County (<U+8D1E><U+4E30><U+53BF>), and Pingzheng Gelao Village (<U+5E73><U+6B63><U+4EE1><U+4F6C><U+65CF><U+4E61>), [[Zunyi]] (<U+9075><U+4E49>). Estimated by Jiashan He (1983) at 1,700 speakers. He (1983) also lists Anliang <U+5B89><U+826F> and Taiyang <U+592A><U+9633> of Renhuai <U+4EC1><U+6000><U+53BF>, Huajiangzhen <U+82B1><U+6C5F><U+9547> and Ma'ao <U+9EBB><U+5787> of Zhenning <U+9547><U+5B81><U+53BF>, Dingying <U+9876><U+8425> of Guanling <U+5173><U+5CAD><U+53BF>, Maixiang <U+9EA6><U+5DF7> near Qingzhen <U+6E05><U+9547>, and Liangshuiying <U+51C9><U+6C34><U+8425> of Qinglong <U+6674><U+9686><U+53BF> as Hagei-speaking places.
*'''Tolo (<U+591A><U+7F57> Duoluo, ''{{IPA|to<U+02E7><U+02E9><U+0294>lo<U+02E5>}}'', White Gelao)''': west-central [[Guizhou]], western [[Guangxi]], southeastern [[Yunnan]], northern [[Vietnam]]; all other '''southwestern''' Gelao varieties. The Niupo variety is also spoken in Machang village (<U+9A6C><U+573A><U+9547>), [[Puding County]] (<U+666E><U+5B9A><U+53BF>), Anshun, as well as Agong village (<U+963F><U+5F13><U+9547>), [[Zhijin County]] (<U+7EC7><U+91D1><U+53BF>), Bijie. The Datiezhai variety is spoken in Gaoshi (<U+9AD8><U+77F3>) of Shuicheng (<U+6C34><U+57CE>) and Miluo (<U+7C73><U+7BA9>) of Shuicheng (<U+6C34><U+57CE>). Estimated by Jiashan He (1983) at 1,200 speakers.
*'''A-uo (<U+963F><U+6B27> A'ou/Ao, Red Gelao)''': west-central [[Guizhou]], western [[Guangxi]], southeastern [[Yunnan]], northern [[Vietnam]] - including Banli (<U+677F><U+6817><U+6E7E>) variety in [[Renhuai County]]; all '''northern''' Gelao varieties, as well as southwestern Gelao of Puding County (<U+666E><U+5B9A><U+53BF>) and Maocaozhai (<U+8305><U+8349><U+5BE8>), Zhijin County (<U+7EC7><U+91D1><U+53BF>). Estimated by Jiashan He (1983) at 1,500 speakers. He (1983) also lists Shawo <U+6C99><U+7A9D>, Xinkaitian <U+65B0><U+5F00><U+7530>, Lannigou <U+6EE5><U+6CE5><U+6C9F> (all in Qianxi <U+9ED4><U+897F><U+53BF>) as A'ou-speaking places.
*'''Aqao (<U+7A3F> Gao)''': west-central [[Guizhou]]; all '''central''' Gelao varieties. Estimated by Jiashan He (1983) at 2,000 speakers. He (1983) also listed Dongkou <U+6D1E><U+53E3> of Shuicheng <U+6C34><U+57CE><U+53BF> and Niudong <U+725B><U+6D1E> of Zhijin <U+7EC7><U+91D1><U+53BF> as Gao-speaking places.
*'''Qaw''': [[Gulin County]] (<U+53E4><U+853A><U+53BF>), [[Sichuan]]; mostly unattested. This dialect is spoken by the Yi (<U+7FBF><U+4EBA>), who are the least-known Gelao subgroup.

The most extensively studied varieties are the Wanzi and Zhenfeng dialects, while the most endangered one is Red Gelao.

===Zhou (2004)===
Zhou (2004) lists four dialects of Gelao.

*'''Hagei (<U+54C8><U+7ED9>)''': Autonyms include ''{{IPA|pu<U+02E6><U+02E8> ha<U+02E7><U+02E5>kei<U+02E6><U+02E8>}}'' (<U+5E03><U+54C8><U+7ED9>) and ''{{IPA|pu<U+02E5> mu<U+02E7>hen<U+02E5>}}'' (<U+5E03><U+76EE><U+4EA8>). Primarily spoken in Renhuai, Zhenning, Guanling, Qinglong, Zhenfeng, and Longlin Counties.
**Pomao <U+5761><U+5E3D><U+6751>, Zhenfeng <U+8D1E><U+4E30><U+53BF>
*'''Duoluo (<U+591A><U+7F57>)''': Autonyms include ''{{IPA|to<U+02E7><U+02E9><U+0294>lo<U+02E7><U+02E5>}}'' and ''{{IPA|t<U+0259><U+02E7><U+02E9><U+0294>l<U+026F><U+02E7>}}''. Primarily spoken in Liuzhi District, Puding, Longlin, and Malipo Counties.
**Qingkou <U+7B90><U+53E3><U+5F5D><U+65CF><U+4EE1><U+4F6C><U+65CF><U+5E03><U+4F9D><U+65CF><U+4E61>, Liuzhi <U+516D><U+679D><U+7279><U+533A>
**Machang <U+9A6C><U+573A><U+5BE8>, Puding (extinct)
**Mengzhou <U+731B><U+821F><U+6751>, Puding (extinct)
*'''Gao (<U+7A3F>)''': Autonyms include ''{{IPA|p<U+0259><U+026F><U+02E5> kl<U+0251>u<U+02E5>}}'', ''{{IPA|p<U+0259>u<U+02E7><U+02E5> q<U+0251>u<U+02E7><U+02E5>}}'' (in Dongkou <U+578C><U+53E3><U+6751>, Houchang Township <U+7334><U+573A><U+4E61>), and ''{{IPA|p<U+0259>u<U+02E7><U+02E5> l<U+0251>u<U+02E7><U+02E9>}}''. Primarily spoken in Pingba, Anshun, Puding, and Shuicheng Counties. Its 4 dialects are Dagouchang <U+5927><U+72D7><U+573A> of Pingba, Xinzhai <U+65B0><U+5BE8> of Puding, Dongkou <U+6D1E><U+53E3> of Shuicheng, and Xiongzhai <U+718A><U+5BE8> of Zhijin (extinct).
**Dongkou <U+578C><U+53E3><U+6751>, Houchang <U+7334><U+573A><U+4E61>, Shuicheng <U+6C34><U+57CE><U+53BF>
**Shuangkeng <U+53CC><U+5751><U+6751>, Puding
*'''A'ou (<U+963F><U+6B27>)''': Autonyms include ''{{IPA|a<U+02E7><U+0263>eu<U+02E7>}}'' (<U+963F><U+6B27>), ''{{IPA|pu<U+02E6><U+02E8> <U+0263>eu<U+02E7>}}'' (<U+8865><U+6B27>, <U+8865><U+5C14>), and ''{{IPA|z<U+0259>u<U+02E7><U+02E9>le<U+02E7><U+02E9>}}'' (<U+67D4><U+52D2>). Small pockets of speakers left in Zhenning, Dafang, and Qianxi Counties. Its three dialects are Bigong, Hongfeng, and Jianshan.
**Shajing <U+6C99><U+4E95><U+82D7><U+65CF><U+5F5D><U+65CF><U+4EE1><U+4F6C><U+65CF><U+4E61>: Tiele <U+94C1><U+4E50><U+6751>, Dengming <U+706F><U+660E><U+6751>, Huangni <U+9EC4><U+6CE5><U+6751>
**Huashi <U+5316><U+77F3>, Qianxi
**Yang'er <U+7F8A><U+513F>, Qianxi
**Longjia <U+9F99><U+5BB6><U+5BE8>, Zhijin
**Mengjia <U+731B><U+67B6>, Puding
**Weicheng <U+536B><U+57CE><U+9547>, Qingzhen <U+6E05><U+9547><U+5E02>
**Maixiang <U+9EA6><U+5DF7><U+6751>, Qingzhen <U+6E05><U+9547><U+5E02>
**Pingzheng <U+5E73><U+6B63><U+4EE1><U+4F6C><U+65CF><U+4E61> (some villages)
**Bayang <U+575D><U+517B>, Puding (extinct)

